Bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with 1/2 tsp of @salt{1/2%tsp}. Halve, peel and thinly slice the @red onion{1/2}. Thinly slice the @chestnut mushrooms{150%g} and @portobello mushrooms{2}. Peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2} (or use a #garlic press{}). Finely chop the @flat leaf parsley{1/2}(finely chopped) (stalks and all). Pour half the @balsamic vinegar{12%ml} into a #bowl{}, add the @olive oil{1%tbsp} and season with salt and @black pepper{to taste}. Mix together and leave to the side.

Add the @penne pasta{180%g} to the boiling water, simmer until tender, ~{12%minutes}. When the pasta is cooked, drain in a #colander{}, pop back into the #pot{}, drizzle with a little @olive oil{} and stir through to stop it sticking together. Set aside off the heat.

While the pasta cooks, heat a drizzle of @olive oil{} in a #frying pan{} on medium heat. Add the mushrooms and @British smoked bacon lardons{90%g} and cook until browned, stirring occasionally, ~{6-7%minutes}. IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat. IMPORTANT: Cook lardons thoroughly. Continue with the rest of the step as instructed. Once browned, reduce the heat to medium-low and add the onion. Cook, stirring frequently until the onion is nice and soft, ~{5-6%minutes}, then add the garlic, season with salt and pepper. Stir and cook for ~{1%minute}. Add the remaining balsamic vinegar, stir and cook until evaporated, ~{1%minute}.

  > If you've decided to add bacon lardons to your meal, add to the pan with the mushrooms.

Pour the @water{150%ml} into your frying pan and stir in the @vegetable stock paste{10%g}. Increase the heat and bring to the boil, then reduce the heat to low and simmer until reduced, ~{5-6%minutes}, stir occasionally. Stir in the @creme fraiche{99%g} until well combined, bring back to the boil and add a good grind of black pepper. Remove from the heat.

Add the drained pasta to the sauce along with three quarters of the @grated hard Italian style cheese{40%g} and three quarters of the parsley. Stir everything together. Taste and add more salt and pepper if you feel it needs it.

Spoon your pasta into #bowls{} and sprinkle the remaining cheese and parsley on top. Add the @wild rocket{40%g} to the balsamic dressing and toss together. Serve on top of the pasta, finish with a good grind of black pepper and enjoy!